  calories: 660 kcal
  fat: 29 g
  saturated fat: 9 g
  carbohydrates: 70 g
  sugar: 13 g
  protein: 33 g
  fiber: 4 g
  sodium: 1060 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/tex-mex-turkey-bowls-5fe12199751960471123e8cc
author: Michelle Doll Olson
time required: 35 minutes
cuisine: Mexican
---

Wash and dry all produce. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @red onion{1}(halved and sliced); mince a few slices until you have @{2%tbsp} (3 tbsp for 4 servings). Drain @pineapple{4%oz}(drained, reserving juice); roughly chop. Roughly chop @cilantro{¼%oz}(roughly chopped). Zest and quarter @lime{1}(zested and quartered). Halve, core, and thinly slice @long green pepper{1}(halved, cored, and sliced into strips).

In small #pot{}, combine @Jasmine rice{½%cup}, @water{¾%cup} (1 ½ cups for 4 servings), and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, in a small #bowl{}, combine minced onion, chopped pineapple, half the cilantro, and a big squeeze of lime juice. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%tsp} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add sliced onion and green pepper; season with half the @Southwest spice blend{1%tbsp} (you'll use the rest in the next step), salt, and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, until veggies are browned and softened, ~{7-9%minutes}.

> TIP: If seasoning begins to brown too quickly, add a splash of water.

Turn off heat; transfer to a medium bowl and cover to keep warm. Wipe out pan.

Heat another drizzle of oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add @ground turkey{10%oz}; using a #spatula{}, press into an even layer. Cook, without stirring, until browned on bottom, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Break up meat into pieces and stir in @Tex-Mex paste{1}, remaining Southwest spice, and reserved pineapple juice. Bring to a simmer and cook until sauce has thickened and turkey is cooked through, ~{2-3%minutes} more. Taste and season with salt and pepper. Turn off heat.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @butter{1%tbsp} (2 tbsp for 4 servings), lime zest, and remaining cilantro. Season with salt and pepper.

Divide rice between bowls and top with turkey, veggies, and pineapple salsa. Drizzle with @smoky red pepper crema{2%tbsp} and serve with remaining lime wedges on the side.